race.description: Criterion Hotel Showcase Super Maiden Handicap
race.comment: ESCARGOES (2) progressive three-year-old gelded over the break. Finished in the minor money at his first two starts on the provincial circuit. Fitted with the two trials and the winkers come off. Hard to stop. UNCLE BARRY (1) Kembla-trained gelding close to shedding his maiden status. Shouldered the 59kg from the good draw when third over 1000m at Kembla Grange. That form looks good enough for this and placed at the trip. ARTFUL LADY (12) rolled forward from the sticky draw on debut when a respectable third over 1200m at Queanbeyan. Sure to take a lot from that hitout and will appreciate the claim again. Leading contender. APPLE EYES (11) fitter after the two career starts and gets every chance from the low draw. Surged late in the heavy (9) going when a courageous fourth in a 1300m contest at Wangaratta. Respect.
